      "File extensions that share TLDs and commonly appear in code/documentation. These are wrapped in <code> tags to prevent Telegram from generating spurious domain registrar previews. Only includes extensions that are: 1. Commonly used as file extensions in code/docs 2. Rarely used as intentional domain references Excluded: .ai, .io, .tv, .fm (popular domain TLDs like x.ai, vercel.io, github.io)",
      "Wraps standalone file references (with TLD extensions) in <code> tags. This prevents Telegram from treating them as URLs and generating irrelevant domain registrar previews. Runs AFTER markdown\u2192HTML conversion to avoid modifying HTML attributes. Skips content inside <code>, <pre>, and <a> tags to avoid nesting issues."
